It's weird, and I like that. The characters singing took me by surprise and was a great moment.

This section of the description doesn't work for me though, or at least the second sentence doesn't.

SCP-2000-A keeps its same background image, which appears to be a young female humanoid with features similar to a white rabbit. This humanoid has its mouth covered in what is presumed to be blood, sharp teeth, and is wearing a red bow on its left ear, and is in front of a pink, spotted background with several small hearts drawn around it.

It's describing an image that we can already see in the article. If it were a photo of a physical 3D object and you were describing the object in the photo, I would understand why you'd describe the object in detail, but everything to describe is in the image, and it's always the same image. I'd say cut the second sentence for length and let the image speak for itself.







